     <h1>Airlines Blog</h1>
     <p><strong>Author :</strong> K . Akhil</p>
     <date datetime="2025-06-01">June 01 , 2025</date>
  
     <p class="intro">Air travel is known as one of the safest 
     modes of transportation. Yet, recent 
     airline crashes have raised serious questions about safety protocols and technological reliability. 
    </p>
 
  <section class="main">
   <h2>The Major Factors</h2>
   <h3>1.Technical Failures</h3>
     <ul>
        <li>System Malfunctions
            Crashes due to engine or autopilot failure.
            One 2024 crash linked to ignored updates.
        </li>
        <li> Old Aircraft
             Aging planes face structural issues.
             Old fleet caused a crash in Africa
        </li>
     </ul>
 
   <h3>2. Weather Challenges</h3>
     <ul>
        <li>Storms & Turbulence
           Extreme weather causing mid-air crashes.
           Radar failed in a 2025 cyclone case.
        </li>
        <li>Low Visibility
             Fog led to landing errors.
             A plane missed runway in 2025.
       </li>
      </ul>
   </section>
